org.timepedia.chronoscope.client.browser
Class Chronoscope

java.lang.Object
  org.timepedia.chronoscope.client.browser.Chronoscope
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.gwt.user.client.HistoryListener, java.util.EventListener, org.timepedia.exporter.client.Exportable
public class Chronoscope
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.timepedia.exporter.client.Exportable, com.google.gwt.user.client.HistoryListener

Factory class and JS API interface for Chronoscope Charts

This class exports methods that can be used by both Java and JS to create and configure charts, as well as being a global sink for History events

createXYDataset

public static XYDataset createXYDataset(com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject json)
Parse a JSON object representing a multiresolution XYDataset into a class implementing the XYDataset interface

The JSON format is as follows: 

 dataset = {
    id: "unique id for this dataset",
    mipped: true,
    domain: [ [level 0 values], [level 1 values], ... ],
    range: [ [level 0 values], [level 1 values], ... ],
    rangeBottom: min over level 0 values,
    rangeTop: max over level 0 values,
    label: "default label for this dataset",
    axis: "an axis identifier (usually units). Datasets with like axis ids
 share the same range Axis"
 }
